<br>
Wizards are the clutch of the group.  A good wizard will know the best times to unload his gun.  When a group has a line of mobs mesmerized, the wizard should burn his mana on the first couple(mafia crowd control).  This makes it easier on the entire group. A wizard can use most of their mana and save any for evacuate if neccesary.<br>
<br>
Wizards are the best class vs. mobs that heal.  A well placed stun or a large DD will prevent many things(such as myconid priests or dragons) from healing themselves.<br>
<br>
Wizard direct damage indirectly heals the group. Instant massive damage eliminates the nead to melee it for that extra time, thus saving hit points and saving healer mana.  A good wizard, imo, should keep their healer's mana full.<br>
<br>
Wizards can attack from long range and their damage is automatic.  This is essential on large raids, when melee classes can often loose sight of the mob, get in each others way, or suffer from a close range NPC attack(such as area effect)<br>
<br>
In some cases, a wizard can use area effect spells to eliminate a large number of mobs.  A few high level wizards and an enchanter can handle huge crowds in less than a minute.<br>
<br>
Wizards can snare. Use bonds of force.(not fizzling shackles)<br>
<br>
Vision spells - bind sight can be very helpful.<br>
<br>
teleports<br>
<br>
See, we do only have a couple spell lines, but the consequences of direct damage are easily overlooked. <br>
<br>
Thats what I see the wizard being the master of.  There could never be too many wizards when you want something dead.<br>
<br>
